CatDescriptText: Cutline of relatd image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 11, 1961, pg. 14 reads:"Planning Spring Meeting - Officers of the McKees Rocks District of the Church of God in Christ, who met recently to map plans for the March 13-18 session, which will be held at Green's Temple, 2330 Centre Ave., are, left to right, first row: Mmes. Carrie O. Kelly, Alberta Davis, Gertrude Green, Josephine Parker and Elder Junius Davis. Second row: Elder Steve Robinson and Mrs. Marie Baylor.  Third row: Ministers Samuel Sellars and John L. Long, Elder L.H. Green, district superintendent; Elder Charles Ware, Mrs. Georgiana Williams and Elder John Boyd. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, first row from left: Carrie O. Kelly, Alberta Davis, Gertrude Green, Josephine Parker, Elder Junius Davis; second row: Elder Steve Robinson and Marie Baylor; third row: Rev. Samuel Sellars, Rev. John L. Long, Elder L. H. Green, Elder Charles Ware, Georgiana Williams, and Elder John Boyd posed in Church of God in Christ, McKees Rocks
